ncd_critic_def.name: Abnormal Flag Critic
ncd_critic_def.description: Determines if a result is positive by looking at the abnormal flag of the result (OBX-8). Does not determine the condition(s) present.

ncd_critic_def.name: Always Reportable Source Critic
ncd_critic_def.description: Determines if the source (via Application and Facility) is one that can be relied on to always send positive results. Does not determine the condition(s) present.

ncd_critic_def.name: Application Facility Filtering Critic
ncd_critic_def.description: Filters out messages based on the Application and Facility.

ncd_critic_def.name: Decided Results Critic
ncd_critic_def.description: Makes a determination of the current result based on previously seen results. Does determine condition(s) present.

ncd_critic_def.name: Message Type Critic
ncd_critic_def.description: Filters out messages based on the HL7 message type (MSH-9).

ncd_critic_def.name: NLP Critic - Text Analyzer
ncd_critic_def.description: Uses natural language processing to determine both if a particular result is positive and what conditions are present.

ncd_critic_def.name: NLP Critic - Numeric Analyzer
ncd_critic_def.description: Uses the numeric value and any ranges present in the result to determine if the result is positive and what condition is present.

ncd_critic_def.name: NLP Critic - Discrete Analyzer
ncd_critic_def.description: Uses a short, discrete amount of text (i.e. positive) to determine if a result is positive and what condition is present.

ncd_critic_def.name: Processing Id Critic
ncd_critic_def.description: Filters out messages that do not contain a certain processing Id (MSH-11).

ncd_critic_def.name: Reportable Condition Critic
ncd_critic_def.description: Uses a longest common substring matching algorithm to determine if one or more conditions are present in the result. If one or more conditions is found, the result is given a positive determination.

ncd_critic_def.name: ICD9 In OBX Critic
ncd_critic_def.description: Searches for ICD9 codes inside the OBX-5 text. This often indicates a DG1 segment that has been transformed into an OBX segment.

ncd_critic_def.name: Report All Critic
ncd_critic_def.description: Looks for conditions which are reported regardless of whether the condition is positive or negative in the message.
